cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.COMM, cs.MA, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on modeling a network of UAV-BSs and analyzing their coverage and rate performance, which falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture.
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper derives approximations for the coverage probability and average achievable rate, which involves information theory concepts such as channel capacity and coding theory.
3. cs.COMM (Communications and Networking) - The paper deals with the communication aspect of UAV-BSs and their impact on the network performance.
4. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) - The use of UAV-BSs as airborne base stations involves coordination and control of multiple agents, which falls under the scope of multiagent systems.
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper involves modeling and analyzing the performance of a system of UAV-BSs, which falls under the scope of systems and control.
